vider, prompts, and parameters for each strategy.\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:348:If you want to run an existing workflow with a different model or tuned parameters, add a new entry to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`. Reuse the same `workflow` and `agent` as the base strategy, and differentiate by appending a space and a descriptor to the name:\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:381:1. **Add a strategy entry** to `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` with the matching workflow, agent, prompts, and parameters.\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:415:Dynamic-access strategies can optionally download library source code, upstream tests, and/or documentation as read-only agent context. This is configured per strategy via the `source-context-types` parameter in `predefined_strategies.json`. Available types are `main`, `test`, and `documentation`. The artifacts are downloaded from URLs in the library's `index.json` (populated by the `populateArtifactURLs` Gradle task) and extracted to `local_repositories/source_context/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`.\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:419:Multiple predefined strategies exist in `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`, each using a different source-context combination:\\n./forge/AGENTS.md:35:- If the change only alters wording or agent instructions, prefer `prompt_templates/` or `strategies/predefined_strategies.json` over Python logic.\\n./forge/AGENTS.md:45:- `strategies/predefined_strategies.json`: declarative workflow configuration such as strategy names, prompt files, parameters, model, and agent selection.\\n./forge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:129:            \\\"Strategy name from strategies/predefined_strategies.json \\\"\\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:166:            raise ValueError(f\\\"Fallback strategy '{FALLBACK_STRATEGY_NAME}' not found in predefined strategies\\\")\\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:78:            raise ValueError(f\\